=== Justfile ===
# snap-project — Cardano protocol project
# Generated by cardano-init. Edit freely.
#
# The top level aggregates the tasks that terminate and compose: build, test,
# clean. Long-running / interactive tasks (watch modes, local devnets, REPLs)
# are per-component and optional — a component exposes `dev` only when it has
# such a mode. Run one directly, e.g. `just -f <dir>/Justfile dev`; list a
# component's targets with `just -f <dir>/Justfile --list`. See README.md.

default:
    @just --list

# --- On-chain (Scalus) ---
build-on-chain:
    just -f on-chain/Justfile build

test-on-chain:
    just -f on-chain/Justfile test

# --- Off-chain (Scalus) ---
build-off-chain:
    just -f off-chain/Justfile build

test-off-chain:
    just -f off-chain/Justfile test

# --- Testing (Scalus) ---
test-integration:
    just -f test/Justfile test

# --- Aggregate tasks ---
build: build-on-chain build-off-chain
    @echo '{{BOLD + GREEN}}✓ Build complete{{NORMAL}}'

# Build the on-chain blueprint first (consumers read ../blueprint/plutus.json),
# then run each component's tests in role order.
test: build-on-chain test-on-chain test-off-chain test-integration
    @echo '{{BOLD + BLACK + BG_GREEN}}  ✓  All tests passed  {{NORMAL}}'

clean:
    just -f on-chain/Justfile clean
    just -f off-chain/Justfile clean
    just -f test/Justfile clean
    rm -f blueprint/plutus.json
    @echo '{{BOLD + GREEN}}✓ Clean complete{{NORMAL}}'

=== README.md ===
# snap-project

A Cardano protocol project generated by [cardano-init](https://github.com/aspect-build/cardano-init).

## Architecture

```
snap-project/
├── Justfile                    # Task orchestration
├── on-chain/                  # Scalus (scala)
├── off-chain/                 # Scalus (scala)
├── test/                       # Scalus (scala)
├── blueprint/                  # CIP-57 Plutus blueprint (drop or build plutus.json here)
└── README.md
```

## Quick Start

```bash
just build    # Build all components (on-chain first, so the blueprint exists)
just test     # Build the blueprint, then run every component's tests in order
just clean    # Remove build artifacts
```

## Development

`build`, `test`, and `clean` run from the top level. Some components also expose
a long-running `dev` — a watch mode, a local devnet, or a REPL. Not every
component has one (it's optional), so check with `just -f <dir>/Justfile --list`
and run it directly, e.g. `just -f <dir>/Justfile dev`.

When a component provisions a local devnet, its `dev` writes the connection
details into `.env` and the off-chain component connects to it automatically;
with no local devnet it falls back to a public provider (Blockfrost). You never
wire this by hand — it follows the presence of `INDEXER_URL` in `.env`.

## On-chain: Scalus

The `on-chain/` directory contains the smart contract logic written in scala.

```bash
just build-on-chain
just test-on-chain
```

## Off-chain: Scalus

The `off-chain/` directory contains the transaction building and submission logic written in scala.

```bash
just build-off-chain
just test-off-chain
```

## Testing: Scalus

The `test/` directory contains integration tests using Scalus.

```bash
just test-integration
```

## Network

This project targets the **preview** network.

=== .gitignore ===
# Build artifacts
/target/
build/
dist/
# Generated code (e.g. blueprint bundled into the off-chain library)
*.generated.ts

# Dependencies
node_modules/

# Environment
.env.local

# IDE
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

=== .env ===
# snap-project — environment configuration
# Generated by cardano-init. Edit freely.

CARDANO_NETWORK=preview

# Chain connection details.
# Populated by whichever component provisions a local endpoint during its
# `just dev` — an infrastructure service, or a local devnet such as Yaci DevKit
# in the testing role. Left empty otherwise, so consumers always find the keys
# at a stable, predictable location and degrade gracefully when they're blank.
INDEXER_URL=
INDEXER_PORT=
NODE_SOCKET_PATH=

